# Legato Platform Architecture — Product-Level .ologic Model
# REQ-LEGA-001: User State Integrity traced to auth, billing/webhook, and database nodes
# Product-level: shows major subsystems and cross-cutting concerns

name: Legato Platform Architecture
version: "2.0"
description: >
  Legato is a voice-to-knowledge SaaS platform. Users speak, Legato transcribes
  and stores structured notes. The killer feature is an MCP server that gives AI
  agents persistent, categorized memory: notes, search, assets, categories, and
  subfolders. Multi-tenant with tier system (trial, byok, managed). Deployed on Fly.io.

logic:
  mode: diagramming
  version: '2.0'
  networks:
    - id: legato-platform
      label: Legato Platform

      factories:

        # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
        # FACTORY 1: Identity & Auth
        # GitHub OAuth + session management + user state persistence
        # REQ-LEGA-001 anchored here — user record is the source of truth
        # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
        - id: identity-factory
          label: Identity & Auth

          machines:
            - id: auth-machine
              label: Authentication Pipeline
              nodes:
                - id: github-oauth
                  type: gateway
                  title: GitHub OAuth
                  description: >
                    OAuth2 flow via GitHub. All users authenticate through GitHub SSO.
                    No local passwords. Receives code, exchanges for access token,
                    fetches user profile (login, id, email).
                  requirements:
                    - REQ-LEGA-001
                  outputs: [user-lookup]

                - id: user-lookup
                  type: decision
                  title: User Lookup & Recreation Guard
                  description: >
                    After OAuth success, looks up user by github_id or github_login.
                    If not found: attempts recreation by searching alternate identifiers
                    before creating a fresh record. NEVER resets tier, is_beta, or
                    Stripe IDs during recreation — preserves all existing state fields.
                    REQ-LEGA-001 guard lives here.
                  requirements:
                    - REQ-LEGA-001
                  outputs: [session-issuer]

                - id: session-issuer
                  type: process
                  title: Session Issuer
                  description: >
                    Issues server-side sessions after successful authentication.
                    Session carries user_id; all tier/beta lookups go back to DB,
                    never cached in the session cookie.
                  outputs: [auth-cookie]

                - id: auth-cookie
                  type: cache
                  title: Auth Cookie Store
                  description: >
                    Stores session tokens. Short-lived, references user_id only.
                    Cold-start and pod restart safe — state lives in the DB, not here.

            - id: user-state-machine
              label: User State Store
              nodes:
                - id: user-db
                  type: database
                  title: User Database
                  description: >
                    SQLite user records: user_id, github_id, github_login, tier,
                    is_beta, stripe_customer_id, stripe_subscription_id,
                    trial_started_at, created_at, updated_at.
                    This is the authoritative source of truth for all user state.
                    Never populated with defaults that would silently overwrite
                    existing tier or beta flags.
                  requirements:
                    - REQ-LEGA-001
                  outputs: [tier-resolver]

                - id: tier-resolver
                  type: process
                  title: Effective Tier Resolver
                  description: >
                    get_effective_tier() — resolves what tier a user actually has.
                    Beta users always return 'managed' regardless of raw tier field.
                    Trial users checked for expiry. Byok/managed tiers pass through.
                    Always reads from DB; never infers from session.
                  requirements:
                    - REQ-LEGA-001
                  outputs: [tier-gate]

                - id: tier-gate
                  type: firewall
                  title: Tier Access Gate
                  description: >
                    Enforces feature access based on effective tier. Trial users get
                    limited note/asset counts. Byok users supply own LLM key.
                    Managed users get full platform access including MCP server.

          # Cross-machine node: auth bridge connects auth pipeline to user state store
          nodes:
            - id: auth-bridge
              type: process
              title: Auth → State Bridge
              description: >
                After session issuance, reads user state from DB to populate
                request context. All handlers receive effective_tier and is_beta
                from this bridge — no stale session data used.
              requirements:
                - REQ-LEGA-001
              inputs: [auth-machine, user-state-machine]

        # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
        # FACTORY 2: Billing & Subscription
        # Stripe checkout, webhooks, subscription state management
        # REQ-LEGA-001 anchored here — webhooks must not reset user state
        # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
        - id: billing-factory
          label: Billing & Subscription

          machines:
            - id: checkout-machine
              label: Checkout Pipeline
              nodes:
                - id: stripe-checkout
                  type: api
                  title: Stripe Checkout Handler
                  description: >
                    Creates Stripe Checkout Sessions for plan upgrades.
                    Associates stripe_customer_id with user record before
                    redirecting. Never creates duplicate customers.
                  outputs: [checkout-success]

                - id: checkout-success
                  type: process
                  title: Checkout Success Handler
                  description: >
                    Processes successful checkout redirects. Upserts
                    stripe_customer_id and stripe_subscription_id into the
                    user record. Does NOT use session data — re-fetches from
                    Stripe and DB to ensure accuracy.
                  outputs: [billing-portal]

                - id: billing-portal
                  type: api
                  title: Billing Portal
                  description: >
                    Stripe Customer Portal session creation. Allows users to
                    manage their subscription, update payment, cancel, etc.

            - id: webhook-machine
              label: Stripe Webhook Engine
              nodes:
                - id: webhook-receiver
                  type: api
                  title: Webhook Receiver
                  description: >
                    Receives Stripe webhook events. Verifies HMAC signature
                    before processing. Routes to event-specific handlers.
                  requirements:
                    - REQ-LEGA-001
                  outputs: [webhook-router]

                - id: webhook-router
                  type: decision
                  title: Webhook Event Router
                  description: >
                    Routes webhook events: checkout.session.completed,
                    customer.subscription.updated, customer.subscription.deleted,
                    invoice.payment_succeeded. Each path updates user state safely.
                  requirements:
                    - REQ-LEGA-001
                  outputs: [subscription-updater]

                - id: subscription-updater
                  type: process
                  title: Subscription State Updater
                  description: >
                    Updates user tier based on Stripe subscription events.
                    CRITICAL guards enforced here per REQ-LEGA-001:
                    (1) If price_id lookup fails (system_config not initialized),
                        preserve existing tier — do NOT fall back to 'trial'.
                    (2) If user is_beta=1, skip all tier changes unconditionally.
                    (3) On subscription.deleted, beta users are never downgraded.
                    Reads existing user record before any write to detect regressions.
                  requirements:
                    - REQ-LEGA-001
                  outputs: [stripe-product-config]

                - id: stripe-product-config
                  type: database
                  title: Stripe Product Config
                  description: >
                    system_config table: maps Stripe price_ids to tier names.
                    Canonical schema has both created_at and updated_at columns.
                    Populated by init_stripe_products_on_startup() at app boot.
                    If missing, webhook handlers preserve user tier rather than
                    silently defaulting to 'trial'.
                  requirements:
                    - REQ-LEGA-001

          # Cross-machine node: billing bridge connects checkout and webhook engines
          nodes:
            - id: billing-bridge
              type: process
              title: Billing Coordination Bridge
              description: >
                Coordinates between checkout flow and webhook handlers.
                Ensures stripe_customer_id is consistent across both paths.
                Prevents race conditions between checkout callback and webhook.
              requirements:
                - REQ-LEGA-001
              inputs: [checkout-machine, webhook-machine]

        # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
        # FACTORY 3: Voice Pipeline
        # Voice capture → transcription → note creation
        # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
        - id: voice-factory
          label: Voice Pipeline

          machines:
            - id: capture-machine
              label: Voice Capture
              nodes:
                - id: voice-input
                  type: input
                  title: Voice Input
                  description: >
                    Browser MediaRecorder API captures audio. Streams or sends
                    chunks to the transcription endpoint. Supports WAV and WebM.
                  outputs: [transcription-engine]

                - id: transcription-engine
                  type: ai
                  title: Transcription Engine
                  description: >
                    Whisper-based transcription (or BYOK path for byok-tier users).
                    Receives audio blob, returns raw transcript text.
                    Managed-tier uses platform-hosted model; byok-tier uses user's key.
                  outputs: [transcript-cleaner]

                - id: transcript-cleaner
                  type: process
                  title: Transcript Cleaner
                  description: >
                    Post-processes raw transcript: strips filler words, normalizes
                    punctuation, segments by natural pauses. Prepares clean text
                    for note creation.

            - id: note-creation-machine
              label: Note Creation Pipeline
              nodes:
                - id: note-extractor
                  type: ai
                  title: Note Extractor
                  description: >
                    LLM-assisted extraction: turns clean transcript into structured
                    note with title, body, tags, and suggested category. Uses user's
                    BYOK key or platform key depending on tier.
                  outputs: [note-writer]

                - id: note-writer
                  type: process
                  title: Note Writer
                  description: >
                    Persists the extracted note to the notes table. Assigns category,
                    embeds tags, links to user. Triggers embedding generation for RAG.
                  outputs: [note-store]

                - id: note-store
                  type: database
                  title: Note Store
                  description: >
                    SQLite notes table: id, user_id, title, body, category_id,
                    subfolder_id, tags, created_at, updated_at. Central knowledge
                    store for all user notes created via voice or direct input.

          # Cross-machine node: pipeline bridge connects capture to note creation
          nodes:
            - id: voice-pipeline-bridge
              type: process
              title: Voice → Note Bridge
              description: >
                Passes cleaned transcript from capture machine to the note
                extraction pipeline. Carries user context (tier, byok key) through
                the full pipeline so each step uses the correct model path.
              inputs: [capture-machine, note-creation-machine]

        # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
        # FACTORY 4: Knowledge Engine
        # RAG engine + MCP server — the core value of Legato
        # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
        - id: knowledge-factory
          label: Knowledge Engine

          machines:
            - id: rag-machine
              label: RAG Engine
              nodes:
                - id: embedding-generator
                  type: ai
                  title: Embedding Generator
                  description: >
                    Generates vector embeddings for notes and assets on create/update.
                    Uses sentence-transformers or BYOK embedding provider.
                    Embeddings stored as binary BLOBs alongside note records.
                  outputs: [embedding-store]

                - id: embedding-store
                  type: database
                  title: Embedding Store
                  description: >
                    SQLite table storing vector embeddings per note.
                    Paired with the note record. Pure SQLite — no external
                    vector DB dependency. Cosine similarity done in Python.
                  outputs: [semantic-search]

                - id: semantic-search
                  type: process
                  title: Semantic Search Engine
                  description: >
                    Brute-force cosine similarity over all user embeddings.
                    Returns top-K notes ranked by semantic relevance to query.
                    Scoped strictly to the authenticated user's notes.

            - id: mcp-machine
              label: MCP Server
              nodes:
                - id: mcp-server
                  type: server
                  title: MCP Server
                  description: >
                    The killer feature. Exposes persistent, categorized memory
                    to AI agents via the Model Context Protocol. Tools: create_note,
                    get_note, get_notes, search_library, list_categories,
                    list_subfolders, upload_asset, get_asset, delete_note, etc.
                    Each tool is scoped to the authenticated user's data.
                  outputs: [mcp-tool-router]

                - id: mcp-tool-router
                  type: process
                  title: MCP Tool Router
                  description: >
                    Routes MCP tool calls to the appropriate handler. Validates
                    user auth on every call. Dispatches to notes, assets, search,
                    categories, or subfolder handlers.
                  outputs: [asset-store]

                - id: asset-store
                  type: database
                  title: Asset Store
                  description: >
                    Stores binary assets (images, PDFs, files) associated with
                    user notes. Referenced via MCP get_asset/upload_asset tools.
                    Per-user storage quotas enforced by tier.

          # Cross-machine node: knowledge bridge connects RAG and MCP
          nodes:
            - id: knowledge-bridge
              type: orchestrator
              title: Knowledge Orchestrator
              description: >
                Connects the RAG engine and MCP server. MCP search_library tool
                calls flow through here to the semantic search engine. Note writes
                from MCP tools trigger embedding generation in the RAG engine.
                Central coordination point for all knowledge operations.
              inputs: [rag-machine, mcp-machine]

        # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
        # FACTORY 5: Platform Operations
        # Admin panel, tier enforcement, Fly.io deployment
        # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
        - id: platform-factory
          label: Platform Operations

          machines:
            - id: admin-machine
              label: Admin Panel
              nodes:
                - id: admin-api
                  type: api
                  title: Admin API
                  description: >
                    Protected admin endpoints: user listing, tier overrides, beta
                    flag grants, state audit. Requires admin session. All mutations
                    log to audit trail.
                  outputs: [admin-user-manager]

                - id: admin-user-manager
                  type: process
                  title: Admin User Manager
                  description: >
                    Handles admin operations: grant/revoke beta status, manually set
                    tier, force-recreate user, inspect raw user state. Beta grants
                    via this path are authoritative — they survive webhook events.
                  requirements:
                    - REQ-LEGA-001
                  outputs: [state-audit-api]

                - id: state-audit-api
                  type: api
                  title: State Audit API
                  description: >
                    GET /admin/api/user/<id>/state — returns raw tier, effective_tier,
                    is_beta, stripe_customer_id, stripe_subscription_id, trial status.
                    GET /admin/api/users/state — same for all users.
                    Used to verify REQ-LEGA-001 compliance after webhook events.
                  requirements:
                    - REQ-LEGA-001

            - id: deployment-machine
              label: Fly.io Deployment
              nodes:
                - id: fly-app
                  type: cloud
                  title: Fly.io Application Host
                  description: >
                    Deployed as a Fly.io app. Single container running the Flask
                    application. Fly.io handles TLS, anycast routing, and cold starts.
                    Volumes mounted for SQLite persistence across restarts.
                  outputs: [fly-volume]

                - id: fly-volume
                  type: database
                  title: Fly.io Persistent Volume
                  description: >
                    Fly.io volume mount at /data — hosts the SQLite database file.
                    Survives pod restarts. Cold starts re-attach the same volume;
                    user state persists across Fly machine cycling.
                  requirements:
                    - REQ-LEGA-001
                  outputs: [startup-init]

                - id: startup-init
                  type: process
                  title: App Startup Initializer
                  description: >
                    create_app() initialization sequence: DB schema init →
                    init_stripe_products_on_startup() → register blueprints.
                    Stripe product config must be populated before webhooks fire.
                    Ensures system_config table is ready so webhook handlers
                    never fall back to default tiers.
                  requirements:
                    - REQ-LEGA-001

          # Cross-machine node: platform orchestrator bridges admin and deployment
          nodes:
            - id: platform-ops-bridge
              type: monitor
              title: Platform Ops Monitor
              description: >
                Monitors platform health — connects admin panel visibility to
                the underlying deployment and database state. Surfaces Fly.io
                volume status, startup init success, and user state integrity
                metrics to the admin panel.
              inputs: [admin-machine, deployment-machine]

      # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
      # NETWORK-LEVEL CROSS-FACTORY NODES
      # Connect the five factories at the platform level
      # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
      nodes:
        - id: platform-orchestrator
          type: orchestrator
          title: Legato Platform Orchestrator
          description: >
            Top-level coordination node. User authentication (identity-factory)
            gates access to all other subsystems. Billing state (billing-factory)
            determines tier, which gates voice pipeline (voice-factory) and
            knowledge engine (knowledge-factory) feature access. Platform ops
            (platform-factory) provides admin visibility and Fly.io hosting for all.
          requirements:
            - REQ-LEGA-001
          inputs: [identity-factory, billing-factory]
          outputs: [voice-factory, knowledge-factory, platform-factory]
